# organization-assets package

Shared **React** library: components, tokens, brand artwork (static files), styles, hooks, utils. Published as `@themusictree/brand` to GitHub Packages. Consumed via subpath imports from `@themusictree/brand/...`.

## Build

- **tsup** compiles TS entry points to `dist/` (ESM + CJS + `.d.ts`). Config: `tsup.config.ts`.
- **Post-build copy:** `src/styles` → `dist/styles/`; brand asset folders → `dist/brand/...`; favicon bundles `src/favicons/...` → `dist/favicons/...`; each `src/banners/<project-slug>/` → `dist/banners/<project-slug>/` (see `package.json` `scripts.build`).
- Run `npm run build` after structural changes; `dev` is tsup watch only (copies are not re-run each save—re-run full build when static files change).
- **`ORG_DOMAIN`**, **`ORG_GITHUB_SPONSOR_BUTTON_URL`**, **all playground social keys**, and **`HTMT_API_SUBDOMAIN`** / **`GTMT_FRONT_SUBDOMAIN`** / **`AUDIOMETA_FRONT_SUBDOMAIN`** in **`playground/.env.example`**: **required** for **`npm run build`** / **`npm run dev`** (see **`scripts/assert-org-url.mjs`**, which merges **`playground/.env`** with the shell). **tsup** inlines those values into published **`dist/`** (lockup, sponsor iframe, **`Social*Link`** defaults, **`socialBuildEnv`** subdomain strings, etc.). **Publish** workflow passes every key—**never treat publish-time env as optional** (see **`.cursor/rules/publish-workflow.mdc`**).

## Adding code or entries

- **Playground (same PR, mandatory):** Anything you add below that ends up in **`dist/`** for consumers must be **visible in `playground/`** before merge. See [Playground (required for every new dist surface)](#playground-required-for-every-new-dist-surface).

- New **TS surface**: add or extend an entry in `tsup.config.ts` and matching `exports` in `package.json`.
- New **static brand assets** under `src/brand/<folder>/`: add `"./brand/<folder>/*": "./dist/brand/<folder>/*"` to `exports` and extend the build script `cp` so files land in `dist/brand/`. Optional **`…-mark-greyscale.svg`** / **`…-lockup-horizontal-greyscale.svg`** / **`…-lockup-stacked-greyscale.svg`** variants live beside the color source in the same folder; see [`src/brand/README.md`](../../src/brand/README.md) — add them only when needed, not for every mark.
- New **favicons** under `src/favicons/<project>/`: expose `"./favicons/*": "./dist/favicons/*"` and ensure the build copies `src/favicons` to `dist/`. Conventions: [`src/favicons/README.md`](../../src/favicons/README.md).
- **Banners:** one folder per project under `src/banners/<project-slug>/` (same slug style as brand/favicons). Conventions in [`src/banners/README.md`](../../src/banners/README.md). Expose `"./banners/*": "./dist/banners/*"` (already in `package.json`); build copies all immediate subdirs of `src/banners/` into `dist/banners/`. The README ships in npm `files`. Full doc map: [`docs/README.md`](../../docs/README.md).
- **TypeScript:** `tsconfig.json` uses `"moduleResolution": "bundler"`—keep it compatible with tsup.

## Playground (required for every new dist surface)

The Vite app under **`playground/`** is the local catalog for published **`dist/`** output.

**Rule:** Whenever you add or change a **shipped surface**—a React export, a static file copied into **`dist/`**, or a **new `dist/` tree**—update the playground in the **same PR**. Do not merge asset or component work that is not reflected there.

**Checklist**

1. Run **`npm run build`** at the repo root (static copies and tsup output must be current).
2. **Components, hooks, or other TS** shipped from **`components`** / **`index`**: add or extend a **demo** in **`playground/src/App.tsx`** (or a colocated playground module)—props, variants, and any required **`playground/.env`** keys documented in **`playground/.env.example`** when applicable.
3. **Static assets** (brand, favicons, banners, or anything else copied into **`dist/`**): the file must appear under the correct **tab** (**Components** demos vs **Brand** / **Banners** / **Favicons** grids). Grids use **`import.meta.glob`** in **`playground/src/distAssetGlobs.ts`** (paths under **`node_modules/@themusictree/brand/dist/...`**). If assets live under a **new `dist/` subtree**, **extend those globs** or add an explicit **`?url` import** preview in **`App.tsx`** so the file is listed or shown.
4. When the auto grid is not enough (e.g. light vs dark lockups), add a **labeled preview** alongside or instead of relying on the grid alone.
5. **Workflow:** **`npm run build`** at the repo root, then **`npm run dev --prefix playground`** or **`npm run playground`**. Playground **`dev`** / **`build`** run **`scripts/assert-org-url.mjs`** first (same keys as root build). If the catalog looks stale, restart the dev server or clear **`playground/node_modules/.vite`**.

Details: **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** (Component and asset preview — playground).

## Publishing

- **Workflow env is all required:** every key in **`publish.yml`**’s **`npm run build`** **`env`** block must be set from repository variables before a release succeeds. See **`.cursor/rules/publish-workflow.mdc`** when editing files under **`.github/workflows/`**.
- Published to **GitHub Packages** via `.github/workflows/publish.yml` (triggers on `v*` tag push). The same workflow creates a **GitHub Release** so watchers can subscribe to release notifications (`Watch` → **Releases** on the repo).
- `package.json` has `"publishConfig": { "registry": "https://npm.pkg.github.com" }`.
- Release process: `npm run release -- patch|minor|major` (bumps version, stamps changelog, commits, tags, pushes). Publishing starts automatically. See `CONTRIBUTING.md` § "Releasing" for full steps.
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` `[Unreleased]` section in every PR. During releases, move entries to a versioned section.

## Scope

- **Clickable UI:** Hover (and focus-visible where applicable) for buttons, links, and icon links — see [`interactive-hover.mdc`](interactive-hover.mdc) and **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** § 3.1.
- Prefer **minimal, focused diffs**; match existing component and import style.
- Published files: `dist`, `docs`, and colocated READMEs listed in `package.json` `files` (e.g. `src/banners/README.md`, `src/brand/README.md`).
- Follow commit message and PR naming conventions documented in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
- **Markdown:** multi-section `*.md` files repo-wide should include a **Table of contents** per [`static-assets-and-docs.mdc`](static-assets-and-docs.mdc) (`CHANGELOG.md` and one-section stubs exempt).
